caption: This satellite image shows a mix of natural and human-modified landscapes. A large, green grassy area dominates the center and lower parts of the image, bordered on the bottom by more densely vegetated, possibly forested regions. To the top right, there is an exposed, barren area featuring a large excavation site, likely associated with mining or construction. A road runs along the left side, near patches of vegetation and a small pond or depression close to the grassy zone.

This satellite image shows a mix of natural and human-modified terrain. In the upper part of the image, there is visible land clearance or construction work, characterized by bare earth and geometric patterns. Below, there are patches of dense, dark-green vegetation spread across lighter green areas that likely represent open grasslands. The contrast between the cleared land and the natural vegetation suggests development or environmental modification in progress.

The satellite image shows a hilly terrain with lush green vegetation, likely indicative of dense forests or woodland. Two small, possibly natural bodies of water are visible on the lower part of the image. The landscape appears relatively untouched by human activity, with no discernible human-made structures or large pathways visible. The topography suggests a mixture of gently sloping areas with steeper, forested sections.

This satellite image shows a coastal area with significant erosion in the form of cliffs or bluffs running parallel to the shoreline. On the left, there is a body of water, likely an ocean or sea, visible with a mix of sandy beach and rocky formations. To the right, there is a developed residential area featuring streets, houses, and green spaces. The cliffside vegetation is sparse in places, with exposed soil visible. The contrast between natural terrain and urban development is striking in this image.

This satellite image shows a mix of urban and agricultural areas. On the left side, there is a clustered arrangement of buildings, likely residential or commercial, with road networks. To the right, expansive green fields dominate the landscape, interspersed with patches of trees and croplands. A large human-made structure in the center, possibly a greenhouse or industrial facility, is visible, along with water features like a rectangular water reservoir nearby. The overall scene reflects a blend of rural and developed land use.

The satellite image displays a landscape divided between green, grassy fields and barren, excavated areas. A road or rail line, flanked by vegetation, cuts through the middle of the image, separating the natural greenery on the left from industrial mining or construction activity on the right. Tree lines and patches of greenery are visible along the edges of the fields and road.

The satellite image shows an area dominated by human-made structures resembling a large excavation or mining site characterized by exposed earth and varying levels of terrain. Dirt roads, large pits, and terraces are present, implying significant industrial activity. Sparse vegetation is visible, particularly in smaller patches of green on the outskirts of the site, contrasting with the predominantly barren land.

This satellite image shows a combination of natural and human-made features. There is a large cleared area, likely part of an excavation or mining operation, with winding dirt roads and exposed soil. Surrounding the cleared land is dense vegetation, primarily grassy areas with some trees, especially on the right side. There is also a paved road visible in the bottom-left corner, indicating human infrastructure.

This satellite image shows a hilly or mountainous terrain with dense forest cover and patches of grassland or open meadows. A few winding roads cut through the landscape, connecting various sections of the area. There are no visible large water bodies or significant urban infrastructure, indicating a predominantly natural environment.

A narrow road runs between the wooded area and a more open, grassy plain on the right-hand side. The vegetation appears lush, with a clear boundary between the forest and the grassland. No significant water bodies or large human-made structures are visible.

Several clusters of trees and what appear to be orchards or plantations are visible in the central area, contrasting with the more densely packed residential zone. There's also a clear boundary between the developed and agricultural areas.
